==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[concatenatus]]''', perfect passive participle of verb '''[[concatenare]]''', ''chain together'', from prefix '''[[con-]]''', ''with'', + '''[[catenare]]''', ''chain'' (verb), from '''[[catena]]''', ''chain'' (noun)

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|concatenat|e}}

# Join or link, especially in a chain.
# ''([[w:Computer Science|computer science]])'' Join sequences (such as strings of characters) into one single sequence.

====Translations====
* French: [[:fr:Enchaîner|enchaîner]]
* Latin: [[concatenare]]